State Pattern
===============================

*The State Pattern* ...

Indications
-----
* A system has behavior that changes depending on conditions.
* Need flexibility to add additional behaviors in the future.

New OO Principles
-------------------
1. ...


Refactoring Steps
-----
* p. 394: The initial code is very procedural/imperative.
* p. 402: Change request to add 1 in 10 winner of free gumball. Need to encapsulate what changes and apply the open-closed principle. Rework to encapsulate state objects in their own classes and then delegate to the current state when an action occurs.
	1. Define a State interface with a method for every action in the Gumball Machine.
	2. Implement a State class for every state.
	3. Get rid of conditional code and delegate work to State classes.
	

